 friend and I, two of us anyhow, for ten years we've been running raffles around the three pubs in the village, all the year round, and when I tell you what we've been given you'll never believe me. The last raffle we done, there's two hundred and seventy
 
pensioners in Tongywnlais, and how much do you think we give them each, for a Christmas box? I'm sorry. Two pound. Five hundred and forty-seven pound we collected in the raffles. See? That's a tremendous lot of money, that's a good work - we've been doing
 
