s an attendant and a - boy by the name of Arthur Rhys, and Tommy Diamond - a bit older than -, he was King Winter. And we performed this in the school. And the blink - and we had - wadding snowballs - to throw at one another. And I can't remember the word
s
 we had to say now, but we had to say some words and throw a snowball, And this blinking night - it actually snowed. And in our wickedness - never mind the - wadding, you know, we got the real snow - snowballs, and were pelting them into the audience. The
r
e was murder over that. But it was - you know, it was all fun and everybody took it at - in the fun. Oh gosh I had a - cantata to perform, Oh it was wonderful. And I - I - I remember a girl - Nancy Brookman her name was - she was very plain looking - and 
s
he wanted a part in this concert. And we give her a part as a fairy. And the big curtains when you go out to front of the stage you know, And my father - keep off the stage. But Francis - opened the curtains to have a peep - the audience roared. When she 
