ea - winter nights, we used to have what we call penny readings. And they'd give - they'd give you a book - for a prize or sixpence for a prize. The best thing - I remember was a - I - this night - in the penny readings there was nobody there, only - I wa
s
 the only one taking part in the age from - eleven to twelve. I sang Dare to be a Daniel. And when the adjudicator went - went to give his adjudication I wasn't even good enough to have a prize. And singing by myself. So I - so you could see what that was
