e
ry - three hundred yards - another four would be waiting in the - in the march - to take over, and they'd carry it probably a mile and a half or two miles, to the cem - to the cemetery, yes. And - first of all they'd take it into the chapel you see. They'
d
 have a service there. And then when they got to the church - it would be a big affair, because - there was beautiful singing. Although not like it is today, just to - well there he is, he's gone, put him in. See and then they'd all go back to the - home,
 
and they'd have - the home you know, and - have tea, and they'd probably hang around the house 'til late in the night. But after that - the mourning then would go on for a couple of days. Oh yes, it was a dad affair. For a funeral, oh yes. And there'd be 
- you could take it from me every - house in the street - if they didn't go to the funeral, they'd have their blinds draw Oh every house in the street would have their blinds drawn. Aye, every -
