t six in the evening. Winter and summer. Come home by eight or nine. Clean the horse, feed the horse, go home for bed and dawn - bat down the next morning. And I'd been with him now - about six months, three and six a week, and my dinner. And my dinner wa
s
 bread and cheese and onion. And there was a step on this cart. And when he was coming out - of the cart, I had to put a butter box in under the step and guide his leg - down there. Well I had been working in Melingriffith for about six months and I knew 
all the boys there. So - they were voting in Edward church. So I had to take him down in this cart - to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When would this have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Let me see now. About 1904. About 1904. Aye, 1902 probably. And I took him down to Woodchester to vote, and i
t were all Liberals in them days. And there were a lot of boys around the vote of course by the school, and I had to get or of the cart, put this butter box - down and guide his leg and on it. And all boys started shouting and laughing at me you know. Wha
t
 are you carrying Griff? So as soon as he had two steps to walk in the school, as soon as he walked in the school I buggered off and run home and left the horse and cart a him there. I finished, I didn't go to work no more. The - they - upset me then by s
hout -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You were only a little boy really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 I was only about - thirteen or fourteen, tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5572000\charrsid13850017 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 's all I was. But -
