 she'd be working all day, we were six children, and then when the night come - she'd sit down and put her glasses on, and perhaps she'd catch hold of the Bible, very rare any other book. But before - she had done half a page she'd gone to sleep, See in t
hose days that was - and my father, working in the tinworks, he'd come home - of course there was a bit of the garden to do and have a look at that. He'd potter round and prim around, and do any little tiny odd jobs. But that was their only recreation.

