work. A truck - a truck would come down the line - with about twelve ton of coal in, small coal. We'd have what they call a ramp - and you'd hit the two front pins out, and - start this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4881359\charrsid13850017 
little motor, and it would lift}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017  the back of the wagon up. And the coal
'd all run down into a grating, for the conveyor to take it up to the washery. But - in the winter - with the front - half of it wouldn't come out. So you had to go - climb up the van - the co - truck with this hand, with a shovel in this one. Digging the
 coal up in and the truck is up like that. And you'd do about sixty trucks a day. Work be God. Ne - hardest work in the world it was.
