 about 1927 - I had become the trade union - representative. They started a trade union there then. And I - I was a bit of a rebel. And when we come out - out on strike, I couldn't go back there. I was victimised and - the organi - this is why I've got no
 
patience - with trade unions, they're the biggest damned frauds in the world, and I can prove it because - I knew Frank Hodges, Bob Smiley, Marty Jones, I knew 'em all. And when I got - lost my job - through - it was a quarrel over time and a third. We wa
n
ted time and a third - for unloading dirty stuff from the washery. And I went to the engineering institute in Cardiff to try to get it. But when we come out on strike - I could - me nor the chairman of the union couldn't go back - back any more. So after 
