hat - in my first job I looked for - I saw a job advertised - pipe jointing, I'd never done it. They were building an estate in Tonyrefail. So I took a job pipe jointing. And it was a - that'd be about thirty or forty navvies - with big - building trenche
s
, digging trenches, and they'd put those six inch or nine inch pipes in, and we'd have to make the joints with lead, run hot lead in the joints you know. Well I'd never done the job when I - so I started off with it. And damn I was very successful. So I w
as there for about two years. And I was - I was really the boss then.
