ly. And Lord Ninian Steward was a proper toff. Mind I - I happened to come in contact with him because - when he came to stay in the Castle my father's brother - was the caretaker there for fifty years. I sang up there for him. I drank up there with him. 
A
nd he used to talk to me on the road and - look for me the next day. And I think myself mind - that I'd have got on very well, but he went - got - joined the Army and got killed see. That was the difficulty there. And - in my opinion - the Conservatives i
n them days, no question about it, they were good. But L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
