d it was - ten out of every eleven would be a Liberal. Ten. And all the remainder would follow Colonel Lewis. There was a bit of class distinction mind about the Liberals and the - and the Conservatives. Oh yes. Oh yes, now you see - you'd get a - a Conse
r
vatives in them days, I don't - today, you'd get the Conservatives, they would be - the schoolmasters, the vicars, or the farmers, you see, that's the people you'd get. You wouldn't get any of them - Liberal. But they wouldn't condemn you because you were
 
a Liberal. And they wouldn't quarrel with you. They'd discuss it with you. But today if you - say - if you said to somebody, well as they do, they say to me - you're a bloody Conservative aren't you? You - I says, aye, why not? But they're willing to quar
rel with you today because they're not willing for you to have your own views. Now I believe in people having their own views, it doesn't matter what you are. But - politics was - was great - politics was great fun in those days mind. Great fun.
