o Town. Went in the pub and - went to the meet the girls, now they were coming from - oh - just outside Bridgend. What the devil the name is - anyhow - no, no. No. No, Kenfighill. They're coming from Kenfighill. Three sisters and a Ray Ellis. And we had -
 
the train would come into the Bay. So we goes to meet 'em in the Bay and - off we went to the dance. And - you know, spending money on 'em mind. Didn't have it to spend you see. Walked back now to the - the station to take 'em back, and the train - the tr
a
in is in the - in the Bay. So - we're in our different carriage you know, having a little spoon in them, and before we knew where we were, damned thing pulled out and took us with it. So - we wound up in Kenfighill. So we had to walk back to Bridgend. So 
w
e are knocking the pub up at three o'clock in the morning, asking to get our horse and cart out. And he's going to kill us. But we gets the horse and cart out anyhow, and home we start coming. And when we come to Lantrisant Common, we are all of us sleepi
ng in the trap, the little pony is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 dawdling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
 along and - on the Lantrisant Common's a lot of stray horses. They started gathering - our little horse and trap run away, tipped the cart, broke the cart and the harness, we got home at eleven - when they were go
