\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, oh aye. I remember - talking abo
ut that now I'd better tell you about this. My mother was - a marvellous woman in making anybody elderberry wine. And she used to make it in those five gallon jars you know. And I had a uncle - living across the Valley there - and he used to come over two
 
or three times every Christmas. And my mother'd say, a - a glass of wine Jim? Yes, Maggie, I'll have a glass thank you. And he - would catch up, oh, beautiful. You can make this all right. So about - this is a couple of day before Christmas. So Christmas 
- Eve - my mother - I said to my mother - we're coming up tonight. Well don't you make a noise then. Right. Me and my four pals come up to play cards of course, after they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 d gone to bed. About - twelve o'clock we got there. Soon as they'd all gone to bed - 
