Oh as a rule, yes, oh yes. Stand. No, no, no. No, no, no, no. Although mind you myself - very seldom I did sit down to breakfast. Mm, very seldom. I'd always stand up - talking and - seeing to
 the others eating my breakfast like that. Yes. But not other meals mind, I'd sit to other meals. But breakfast I was never fussy about sitting down to it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you have regular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You wouldn't sit at the same place each meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who would the meal be served by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh either of us, if the wife wasn't well I'd serve it, if she was all right she'd serve it herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How would you feed and seat the children too young to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 W
ell - well we'd feed 'em - I'd feed - if the - if I - if the wife was all right - she'd feed 'em, if not well I'd feed 'em. They'd sit by us, by the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you have a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, we had a high chair, yes. We had a high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When did they join in family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What do you mean now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When would the babies join in with the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh as soon as they could sit down, eighteen months old, they'd sit down to the table and - yes, we'd look after 'em. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When your children were young did you feel that there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh well there's all - there's always the right way to bring 'em up. I - I always thought that that - I never believed - in children having their
 own way. If it was something wrong. I believed in - I always - warned 'em and told them - what they ought to do, and I expected 'em to do it after I told 'em, and they used to. I never had no - trouble with my children in things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you and your wife have the same ideas about bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Or different ideas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. We had the same ideas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you talk about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Very often. Very often, and - very often. We would discuss the children o
ften And we used to - and - and after they grew up a little bit you see - when they were - big enough and able enough to go to a place of worship, we seen they went. But, I remember my eldest boy, or the second one was it - he'd go to chapel with his moth
er and I on a Sunday night, and - you wouldn't hear him all night because he took a needle and cotton and a bit of rag with him, and he'd s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 w in chapel all night. Yes. Sew, sit down and sewing, a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What would he sew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Anything. Aye, so - and wh
ile he had the needle and cotton you wouldn't hear him. But don't take it off him. No, I never worried and - I never - if he wanted that way, there you are, that's what he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did he used to do any sewing in the house, mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 It was just play with him was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Play with it, that's right, aye. Aye, when - and when he was three or four - four - three, four and five year old. Oh aye, it was nice when he - he - he'd sit down for hours with a needle and cotton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
My mother-in-law, she was very good you know - nice pleasant woman, and - if I thought there was anything wrong - I'd discuss it with her and I - see what she - thought - thought about it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 This was your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. 'Cos my mother wasn't living by us then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Your mother was alive was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh about once a fortnight. Used to come down from Tonyrefail about once a fortnight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ask her advice at all in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Yes. Very often. Very often, but when - you see my mother - she had - grandchildren living next door to her, both sides, and - she was always sewing and
 making for them. Making clothes for the children always. And I never worried her much about my own. We could carry on and do what we want to do ourselves, but if I felt that I ought to ask her something, I'd ask her anything I wanted to know and - oh she
'd - discuss it with me and tell me what she thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you had she have the same ideas on how to bring up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well no, I wouldn't say we did. No, because you see I'm - I'm a very - very funny man, I don't believe - today even - I don't b
elieve in children when they're able to go out - to run out - and run and play and go anywhere and - come back when they felt like it. Well my children was going out, I'd say well now where are you going? And don't come back here after half past six or se
ven o'clock. And if they weren't there at that particular time, I would be looking for them. And I - the same today. I don't believe in my grandchildren - going out - and you don't know where they are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You did mention that your mother in law was alive and you did used to take to her quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Every day. Living close by us, ah. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And you asked her advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you and she have the same ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Ye
s, we did. Yes. Yes we did really. She was a very pleasant woman. And - not - not like - you - you see some of them today, spoilsports, she'd love the children to have a bit of fun and love the children to play. But in reason, everything. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Can you tell me some of the things that you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well - you see, my - my pint - was always that - you brought them into the world, a car if you understand me is something like a child to me, I believe in - a motor car.
 You buy a motor car. Well you want to treat it - from the beginning, as a child. Nurse it. And I believe that all children - and my own especially, I used to watch over everything they did and everything they didn't do, and if I thought they were doing s
omething that - they shouldn't do, I would just tell them. But - I - I was very fortunate, we were anyhow, we never had any trouble with our children. Never. They - be bad, they were - they weren't wicked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you like to show them affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about their safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh aye. They never went anywhere without me anyhow. And as I told you, if they went out in the night - and they were supposed to be back - I - I re - I can go back now and tell you about my son. He's courting. No
w - about twenty - twenty I think he is, and I - this night he - he said to me, how - asked me for the lend of the car to take his young lady home, only a mile and a half. I said yes, go on. Half past nine. And - I said - come straight back. Half past nin
e he went and - we were sitting down in the house. Look at the clock, ten o'clock. I said, where is he now? So I had another car. So - five past ten and he hadn't come and I jumped in the car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 I - came down to the Pantmawr road to look for him. His ca
r wasn't there so I knocked at his young lady's door. And she came to the door. I said, where's Travis? Oh well I'm awfully sorry, she said, but when we got by here there's a young lady taken ill across the road here, and the mother run across to ask him 
if he'd run her to the infirmary, to St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
s. So she said, we couldn't do nothing else, and - he's gone to the St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
s with her. So I jumped in the car and went down to St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 s now, and he was in the yard in St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 
