\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well I always brought them up to - to - always told them - always thei
r - honour their - our - their parents, and their - grandparents. And always remember - that whatever they thought - chapel - as a place of worship was a most important place for them to start their life in. And they did. And they did. And I never remembe
r them - when I say - wicked and fight with other boys, that's another matter. But I never remember 'em doing a dirty thing at all. And I never put my finger on one of them in my life. Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You never had to punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What if they did something that you really disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh, well - well - well - oh well I suppose if it had came to a point - point - point like that - if I had to give 'em a tap I would have given - would given it 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Do you remember ever giving them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No, no. Chastising them scores of times and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well - you know - when they promise them they were going somewhere - all right, I told you not to do that, all right, well you're not going and that's the end of it. And - that's right, withdraw some and that's the end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would it be your or Mrs Griffiths punish them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 But she wouldn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You were the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14955578\charrsid13850017 disciplinarian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, I would. But she would - she'd be - agreeable to what I was doing mind. Oh yes, whatever -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would she discipline them herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Oh yes, aye. And the funny thing about it you know, that they'd listen more to her than they would to me. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well because - they kn
ow that I'd - chastise 'em and tell 'em now - don't forget, that's the last time. But ten minutes after I'd forgotten all about it. I never held nothing not more than ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 minutes. If you - if I had a row with 'em now and told 'em well - I wouldn't say now 
- remember that, and keep at them for weeks or days. Once I had told 'em and had it out with 'em - we were good friends straight away. And I believe in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about Mrs Griffiths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh well, she's - incli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 ed to hold it. Yes, inclined to hold i
t for - a day or two. Very - if they done something like - and - and she'd - be - well let's put it this way, she'd be spiteful, with 'em for a day or two 'til - she had had her pan out. Oh yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you tell them that they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Always told them - always told them like this, if anybody your own size or a bit bigger than you - hit you, hit 'em back, and if you think they're going to hit you hit 'em first. Always told them that. Oh yes, they weren't ba
bies because - oh God no. No, no, they could hold their own with any of 'em. And I believed in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. Not until they got - up to fourteen or fifteen years of age. And then 
there was a time that I - there was a family lived in our village - very bad characters, and - the parents were bad people, well - I told them never ignore them, but don't make friends of them. Because I didn't want my boys - to do the things they were do
ing. See they were always - not making - not doing any little bit of mischief, they were doing - dangerous things. And I wouldn't allow that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Just one particular family was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh only one partic - but anybody else they played with who they liked. See, we never had no trouble with 'em playing with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both you and Mrs Griffiths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well I should -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Or did one of you play a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well, no, I - I - no, I - I think we - no, I think they looked up to the two of us, because - I can't bring - I can't put this all - you see, we were very kind parents, got me? Our children were our gods in them days. Well for instance we had a doctor 
in the village there, and his wife, she was a matron in a hospital before she got married. And - they lived not far from us. And she used to say - oh - there's a wonderful father. You'll never see him without his children, he's with them everywhere. I've 
s
een him go to the cinema carrying on my back and carrying the other in my hand, walking a mile with them. Oh no I believe that - see - we - I've listened to parents now. Chastising their children. Four and five - oh - they have been cursing them and smack
i
ng them across the head, kicking 'em going up the road here. Now that's - that's not bringing children up. There was nothing like that in with me. Oh - lord alive no. I remember my - my boy when we was in Tonyrefail, he was - six around, and he came to To
n
gwynlais to stay with my sister, on his August holiday And my mother lived next door mind. My sister - the other sister lived next door there, and they had four boys. And he came down to stay with them. And he - had to coax him to come, he wasn't going to
 
come. Well - I used to phone in the morning - where's - Tab? Oh he's here. Put him on the phone then. They had a phone in the house. He was a sanitary inspector. And I'd say, hello, all right love? Yes. Now be a good boy. Now I'd phone again later on. I'd
 
phone dinnertime. And I'd phone in the - and it was no good for my sisters to say to me - in the night if I phoned about six - for her to say to me - oh he's outside. I want to hear his voice. And I would took. If I was on the phone half an hour I'd wait 
'
til he came. Oh aye. And although he only - he was only by here, when I - we had to come and fetch him on the Saturday - it was like as if we were going - for a grand holiday you know, to rush down to fetch him. And he was the same when he met us to come 
home too don't bother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did your wife work at all after having the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When the children had a birthday would it be different form any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh aye, we'd have a little party and everything, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did they have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, and what you could afford in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Have anything different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh gosh, aye, of course, we made a - make a wed - a birthday cake for 'em and - jellies and trifles, and oh yes, we'd make 'em -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh only a couple of children - whichever the children were perhaps'd have half a dozen or eight - children to come into tea with 'em.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Can you remember anything you did with your wife and the children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - let's p
ut it to you this way. Christmas morning, the children would be up - five o'clock. They'll be on our bed - with whatever toys they had, playing in our bedroom 'til we'd be awake. We'd get up now and come down and then they're looking at their presents, li
k
e if we hadn't seen 'em before naturally, and I believed mind - in keeping Santa Claus as - as Santa Claus too. And I'd say - oh - fancy him coming down, I never heard a thing, see, never heard a thing. And we'd - have breakfast, and then we'd be out on t
h
e road - playing whatever toys they had, and into my mother's with 'em. Showing mother what they had, and into my sisters and - their children be coming into my place. It would be a morning of - excitement all round you know. Then after dinner - if it was
 a lovely fine day, we'd go for a walk up the woods, with the children. And - if there was snow about - we'd go out snowballing. Oh we'd make it a - a jol - a good jolly occasion that day. And - plenty of fun used to have. And then -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. And - I had a violin, a piano and a concertina. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who were the players?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - nobody to be honest with you. In them days, could play the piano, I could play the concertina, and my youngest boy 
- my eldest boy - was learning the violin. But you see - my - my mother lived - in Ton - Tongwynlas here and here we used to come - for - every Christmas evening, we'd have a party in there and have - young couples dancing on the - clear the rooms out, it
 was a jollification all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You'd come down to Tongwynlais at Christmas would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 That's right, all our family - would mix up together then. All of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about your house in Tonyrefail, did you have any musical instruments there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, piano, and I tell you that I had that was my own, yes. And I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you sing in your house, would you and Mrs Griffiths sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, in the - well no, no, no, that's a lie. Her father and mother were living in the same street. So - h
e was a - musician her father, and the wife was a singer too mind. And we used to go down there of a Sunday night, and we'd all be around the organ, they didn't have a piano, they had a organ. We'd be around the organ, singing and - enjoying ourselves.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 So you and Mrs Griffiths would go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 That's right, we'd go there, yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What would happen then when you had the children small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - oh we'd go down with the children. Oh lord aye, 'cos they had children themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 So you would make music together quite a lot?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh god aye. What? Music was our lives. Yes. And when we come down of course, god - even on a - ordinary Sunday night - there was - no in the - take the summer now when we lived back here now - an ordinary sum
mer night, all the family - about twenty of us mind, mother and father - and my sisters and their children, we'd all go walk up Castle Road, or very near to Black Cock about a mile and a half away for a walk on a Sunday night in the summer. Come back, all
 around the piano then. Singing hymns and - having a jollification, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you play any games with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh, I played - played every game with - I had cricket sets, billiards for them. We played everything you know with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You mentioned that you had boxing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh boxing, aye, I box - boxing gloves from a very young age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did your wife join in the games or did she play different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh no, she joined in, oh no, no, she joined in with us. Aye, she'd have 
a go at anything. But - when I look back at 'em now, they were mar - they were marvellous days too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were there any books, newspapers or magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. Books, oh yes, books, aye. I used to be very fond - of - detective stories. I use
d to - and the children always had - plenty of - books you know - Jack and the Beanstalk and all that sort of book. The annual, they always had plenty of annuals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 One newspaper, never took anything else. I used to take the - Morning paper, and later on I went into the Echo instead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Never - oh - oh only about two I think, the Woman - what was the other one? I used to take two magazines, a Woman and something it was. That's all. Never spent a lot of money on papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Where did you get the books from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 A paper shop in the same street as us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - I had a - car, and perhaps used to have a run down as far as - Southerndown, Lampton Major or Porthcawl, or Barry. Spend the day
 there on the sands and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 For a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
The only time I ever went away for holidays - I went to Porthcawl with the two youngest children. And - I had booked up in Conways, in the Main Street t
here. And there had been a mishap - in the booking. And that's my first holiday then, and it was my last. I slept in the bath all the week. They had booked - had overbooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Bed - well the children had the bed with their mother. They had - they're - they're overbooked there and - I had to sleep in the bath.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Only a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Porthcawl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why did you choose to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well because that was the nearest place that we could - what - thought we'd like to go to. And be able to afford it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh - play - down on the sands, and they used to have a fair there. On the fair, but you see - if you had five shillings you could go down the fair
 - you could have a devil of a good outing on five bob see because things were only a penny, and tuppence. A ride on the horses and the sw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 tch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 back'd be - so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How did you manage sleeping in the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh, oh. Bedclothes in there, I can see that 
now. Dear, I cursed the place to pieces. I had speculated and bought a new mac, and it was only three pound but it was a beauty mind. Damn well lost that in the train going down. Well that was the start - start of the holiday. It was one of the holidays I
'll never forget as long as I live.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well, Saturday morning - work you know, we worked first thing Saturday morning always. Come home - about half past eleven, and have dinner, wash and cha
nge. And go out to garden and do some of it and then - we were living - in Tonyrefail of course, we were living about a mile and half this side of Tonyrefail, and then I said, coming up then Lil? No, she said, I don't feel - right o, so I'd take the boy w
i
th me then, and we'd go up to Tonyrefail. And I used to do a bit of overtime in the works, and I never believed in putting that bit of money - in the - box, that was my personal money. And - I think I had about three or four pounds of this money. And I we
n
t into a clothe - a drapers shop there, gents, Bibby his name was, old bachelor, he was about fifty-five, and I knew him well and we were talking there, and he said, I've got a lovely little suit to fit that boy. I said, what is it? A sailor suit it was. 
A
nd I never forget it, it was nineteen and eleven. So I said, I'll have that. We tried it on him, I said, leave it on him. So then I went from there to - Arthur - in the next store, and bought him a pair of - shoes. And a pair of socks. And there he come h
o
me now from Tonyrefail, bought a couple of things to come home, and we come home to Tonyrefail - from Tonyrefail and he looked smart. And - I knocked at the door like and I stood one side, I said, let your mother come and see you. And when she come to the
 
door she very near had a fit. But he looked lovely in it. Aye. I used to do things like that, I remember a - she wanted a pair of shoes one time. And I said, come to Tonyrefail and get a pair yourself. No. Do you remember those shoes? With laces or button
s
 up to here you know. They came in. And I went to this shop and I saw a lovely pair of shoes there. I said, how much? Twenty-five bob, and that - do't make any mistake, that was a tremendous price for shoes then. So I bought 'em. Oh and they were beautifu
l on and fitted her lovely. But you could get damned tired putting 'em on. By the time she'd bent down to lace 'em up - they were up to here see on. Yes, oh gosh, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Back in fashion now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh - aye, I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about Sundays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well, Sunday - was - a religious day with us always. Sunday morning - I'd get up and - prepare the dinner, and the wife - the chapel were only a - oh - four or five hundred yards from us. She'd walk to the chapel with the children, and I'd get the di
nner ready. Then she'd come out and then when she'd come from chapel she'd call in her mother's like and - call in her sisters and then she'd come home, and the dinner'd be all ready now. And - she'd undress the children and - they'd go and get any toys t
h
ey had out and play on the floor, and then - put the dinner out and then we'd have our dinner. Then after dinner, we'd sit down talking and - no television then of course. And - then we'd get ready for Sunday school. And we'd go for - go to Sunday school,
 
and then we'd go for a walk on Sunday school around - back home and we'd have our tea, and then we'd go to chapel. And then after chapel we'd come back, around the road for a walk, call in her mother's and father's, probably have a sing-song there and the
n - home and to bed. That was the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you or the children put different clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh, always changed when you come from chapel. Lord aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You had special clothes for chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Always, oh yes, always kept clothes for - Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you change in between the services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh no. No, no. No, the children would mind. Oh - we wouldn't, but the children would. And - you wanted to you see because - you couldn't expect them to sit down for a couple of hours - without making a bit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday, or did you think it did not matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well, it did matter to me, and I - and I - did think it was wrong, without - it was essential. Now I didn't believe - in coming home and papering yo
ur room. I didn't believe in doing - I didn't believe in going to the garden on a Sunday. Oh no, I didn't believe in any of that. And I - I wouldn't - I wouldn't profess to be a big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 C}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 hristian mind. But - no, working on a Sunday - of course when it come to 
- had to go to the colliery had that coke oven to work - whether you liked it or whether you didn't, it was a seven day a week job, you had to work on a Sunday. But when I say this I don't mean - what I mean is if there's a man - building a house over by 
there. When Saturday twelve o'clock come, I believed in him finishing 'til Monday morning. There's no point in going to work on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you allow your children to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, when they were young, yes, play in the house. But not out
. Not out on the road. No games on the road. Play in the house if they wanted to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What denomination did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well Baptist I was see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Every Sunday and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Your wife went to the same chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, of course you did. Yes, and my wife. And her father was conducting the choir to be honest with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did the chapel run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were you a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No, I didn't join the temperance club. Well I never was a teetotaler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh well - what they had - what they call the young peoples meetings you know. I used to belong to that. And we had a drama - I belonged to 
that of course. But - I - I - I - perhaps I went - two years and I never had a drink. But if somebody came up, a friend of mine and said to me, come and have a glass of beer with me, oh I'd go. But not on a Sunday mind. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were there a lot of activities with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh yes, aye. We - aye, we - were - we were always - we were always doing something, and we had a - Sunday school saving bank, and I was the treasurer of that, and - two nights a week you can say that we had - what they called penn
y readings, and practice for the drama, and the choir. And we used to perform dramas and - little cantatas and all that up there. Oh very active in the church in them days. And - my wife happened to be a - a very good singer then, and - she would be takin
g
 part in everything. Oh dear - very happy start you see this was. Don't make any mistake see, I was a - a blighter before I got married you know. I used to love to bowl about - before I got married. But after I got married I didn't bother, I - only as I t
ell you, I wouldn't tell you that I was a teetotaler for I wasn't, but I'd go two years perhaps and didn't have a drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You mentioned that the children went to Sunday school and they also went with you to family services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
No. Sometimes but very seldom. No. I didn't - it isn't I don't believe in that - but I didn't think it was necessary. With little children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, sometimes, oh yes. Yes, but not very ofte
n. But I - what will I say, I believed in keeping the home - a very happy go lucky - place see. And I believed in the children - looking at life - in a very bright way. I don't be - didn't believe in putting any serious things in their no}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 dles, and until t
hey were old enough to understand. In a way, I'm a very - firm believer in this, I don't believe in when children are four, five and six year old, to begin to teach them the Bible. No, no, no. My policy is this, you teach 'em to follow you, and do what we
 are doing, as long as we are doing right, and if they keep on doing that until they can understand the Bible themselves, then give 'em the Bible to read. See? I don't believe in giving 'em something to read -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 But they used to go to Sunday school did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh, never missed. They had all the training - from the Sunday school teachers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh lord, they never mi-s now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who taught them to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 I did, and their mother. They never - they always - now at their age, they never go to bed without saying their prayers, neither do I.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh aye, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What were your views?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Liberal. But there was one time that I was Labour. But I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 disillusioned
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017  with 'em and - I thought there were no honesty in - the trade union movement and the Labour party, so I turned to - our old friend L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 oyd George.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well because - because I' - believed in L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 oyd George's policy. L}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
oyd George - whichever way those people look at it today, when he became Prime Minister of this country, he had something - that was for the poor people and for the working class. But he didn't have the facility to bring it out. But he did do the best he
 could do, he brought the first little scheme out - for - a four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
penny week - pension and a - medical treatment. He did do that here and I believed in his policy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about your wife, was she interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, not - you see - she used to - listen to a bit of it but - she wasn't interested in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What were her views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 She was the same as my own. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why do you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well because I don't think she was that interested in it you know, she was not in - not int
erested in politics. Mater of fact - she didn't understand much about it. But I read a lot. And - and - and today - I've got stupid ideas today you see. I've got an idea today that this country would be the most prosperous country in the world - if we sac
ked every bugger we've got in Parliament, and picked a coalition government of the best brains in the country. I think we'd have the finest country in the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Do you remember if you voted in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What party did you vote for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh - Liberals. And - a day of pleasure it was. Good God. We'd be out in the night waiting for results, singing on the roads and - it was a pleasure - it was - it was a happy day, not like today. They're damned fighting o
ne another before we start today. But in them days you know - and you see if - if I was a Liberal, and the next chap by me was a Conservative - or a Labour - like would say, well you're going to lose today boy and - that's the end of it, we were all good 
f
riends. But today if you were - somebody - if you say - well I'm a Conservative and - what the hell have you got to be a Conservative - this is it you see, no. They were happy days mind and - I don't know what to think, but today I - I listen to - read th
e
 paper you know, oh - people are here today couldn't live in my day. They couldn't live in it. See, but as I tell you - I've got to be honest about it, I don't blame anybody - only - the government, that's all, because - they have made it so easy today - 
f
or young people to have money - that they don't do any work for it, they get damned good wages and no work and when they come home in the night - they're as fresh as when they go in the morning, and they want somewhere to - see, this is it, they've got - 
too - too much energy. They haven't worked hard enough, to take any energy from them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever feel any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, oh yes, yes. Oh yes, there were lots of people I mean - when I came back to
 Tongwynlais you know - the Conservative party was - strong here. My gosh, all your life. They had a lot of people, we had a wonderful Squire in the village, old Captain - Colonel Lewis. Not him, but his - aids, they'd be - pressuring you if - you don't v
ote mind you won't get this, you won't do that, you won't do the - oh yes. But not the - Colonel himself. But those that were agents and so f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 rth you know. Oh lord you'd have some pressure mind. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about in Tonyrefail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Ay? No, in Tonyrefa
il you had pressure on the Labour party. You did have - and you did, you - look, if you worked in the colliery - and they knew you were a Conservative, by gum. They'd make everything in the world - make it practically impossible for you to stop in the job
.
 Yes. They were the rottenest lot I've ever met in my life. They - you - prejudiced against you. They'd make every - and your own mates, if they knew you were - and don't make any mis - they weren't what I call - Labour. They were damned Communists, not L
a
bour - Labour. And they - you couldn't live with 'em. If they had a chance to get you the sack my girl they'd get you the sack. OH lord, I know lots of people - that are staunch Conservatives, but they wouldn't say. They were pretending to be Labour. But 
they were Conservatives. Oh you had plenty of pressure from the - Labour - Labourites in Tonyrefail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. Worked for the Liberals. Yes, I worked for Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about your wife?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh no, she'd never take any part. No part in it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, always. I - I did go around speaking - for A.B. J
ones - he was a member for the - up the Valleys. I went ground to meetings speaking for him years and years ago. Oh yes, I - done a lot - for the Liberal party. And then I - you get, if you understand me, you get di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 llusioned about the whole damned lot of
 'em. There's something in every one of 'em, that's rotten, you see, this is the point. You get a man and you say oh God, you're here, this is the man. And then later on you can see it - going backwards and backwards and now you're beginning - same as L}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 oy
d George. A wonderful man but you look at - when you come back and look at his character after - isn't it. This is it. And you get 'em like that - now, you see now, Churchill in my opinion see - was undoubtedly one of the finest men in the world of ours s
e
e, never mind about this country. Whichever way you look at it, in my opinion, he was - and here's another man, although he's Labour, I think he's a wonderful man, is Roy Jenkins. I think Roy Jenkins' a damned good man. But Harold Wilson I wouldn't give h
im a cup of cold water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When you and your wife were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well, she'd probably be darning or knitting, and I'd be fiddling around doing something about the house. There was always plenty to do about the house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever go out together in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh lord, aye, yes. I told you about us going out in the horse and cart didn't I? Oh damn, I - of course I was such an active bloke. I - I was - in a way I was a fool - I'd buy horses 
mind. I had five or six horses. Oh yes, and I had - cars. And I'd always be - buying and selling horses or buying and selling pigs, without my job mind. I had a shop and all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 In Tonyrefail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What selling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Drapery and grocery - grocery - grocery and greengrocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 In the house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, in a proper shop, I had a shop. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 While you were still in the colliery?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. Aye, the wife - used to look after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 This was later on though, after 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. Aye, oh after that. Oh lord aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How often would you and Mrs Griffiths go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh very often. Three of four times a week probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh only up around the fields and - up the - you know, 
anywhere around for a walk. And we were very fond of the - pictures in them days you know. All the serials you know. And we used to go and see old Pearl White and oh God, we'd sit down for hours in the pictures, and take the youngest two children with us 
- two children with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When did you get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh well that was all according, sometimes I'd get home dinnertime. And sometimes - I never worked day work you see. All the jobs I ever done was piecework. And - and I could 
go to work and - I could work four hours sometimes and - earn enough to say well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You always worked piecework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 So you could finish when you'd earned enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Never - when I wanted to. Perhaps you'll never believe me but you've seen those big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017  coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
trucks of - small coal haven't you? Well there's twelve ton in them. Would you believe me if I told you that I used to unload them one and six a truck? One and six a truck. With a shovel. Aye, two of us, two pals. And we - I've seen 
us doing twenty trucks - in eight hours between us. It was - that was fifteen bob each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How many evenings a week would you spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh every evening. Never go out without my wife. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever go to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Institutes or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No. No, not then, not in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Aye, belonged to a saving club. We had a saving club in the work and a saving club in the - chapel as well you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What savings club was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Just ordinary works, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Not a funeral or sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, oh lord no, never belonged to anything like that, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did either of you take part in any sport, you or your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, I played cricket, I played foo
tball. I played cricket for the chapel, the chapel had a cricket team you see. I played cricket for the chapel and I played football with a - the minister of - chapel opposite, he had a - a football team. I played for them. Oh yes. Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Shooting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Shooting, aye. Yes. But not fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What would you shoot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Rabbit, pheasant. Oh - many times I've - gone out on a Saturday - then - there were times you understand me now - don't think this is all - there
 were times - that when you'd come to Saturday, you'd say to yourself, well how the devil are we going to manage this weekend? See, well I tell - never mind meat. Go out and shoot a rabbit see. Oh there were - sometimes it was very bad times going along t
hen as well as good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. Not one of us ever - done any bicycling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You mentioned that you went walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Aye, and not - no, never racing, oh no. Either in the trap - or walking or in the car. We always went around like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did either of you bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No damned fear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Very seldom. There were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh - no cinemas, oh concert, any concert going on yes. And there 
were no theatres ever only a - cinemas we used to go do you see. Used to go to the cinema.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes - ah no, there were no music halls here mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 There were only cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 That's right, the cinemas and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And you'd have the chapel concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh yes, chapel concerts and - and there were - in Tonyrefail mind there was a couple of - nice male voice - parties then. And there was Williams All Male Voice and - oh we had a - had a full life in every - everything like that mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Hobbies? Well what did you call hobby now? I call everything a hobby, I mean, the garden was a hobby of mine. And - horses -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Keeping the pigs really was wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Of course it was. 'Course it was and horses and there hobby wasn't it. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did your wife have any other interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, I don't think she did. No, I think the home was her interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did your wife ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. Not without me, we went out - we went out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did anyone outside the home help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 If your wife was ill, you mentioned earlier that she was not well often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 If she was in bed you'd do everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You had relatives living near? You had her sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And - yes, and her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Living in the same street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How much of them did you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh we saw them every day. But they never done nothing for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Where would you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh we either called there or they'd be on the street or they'd call in our place perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 They wouldn't come and help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Didn't - well we never wanted them to, never asked them to. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh plenty of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Where did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Aye. Well they'd be passing, they'd call in. But we were never in the habit of - we'd meet 'em in the chapel or meet 'em in the - meet 'em somewhere we were going. But - we never went about - with any o
ther people, just ourselves, our own family see. My father-in-law and his family lived about ten doors away from us. And then - my wife's uncle was living in the same street as us. But - the friends that we always met - was when we went to - chapel or - i
f
 we went to one of the - different things that was on in the chapel. And you would meet them out but we never went - made a point - an appointment with 'em - to go anywhere. We always kept to ourselves, my - and of course we - we were very fond of childre
n you see. And wherever we went - the children were only a year or two old, but they went with us. We didn't bother to have friends, we had friends coming in occasionally of course, the same everybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you share the same friends, you and your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. More or less, yes, we did. I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have any friends of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
No, because when I went - to live - in Tonyrefail - I had to make - friends there because - my friends was home here in Tongywnlais. But I soon made frien
ds mind. And - I was always interested in horses and cars. And - you pick up different friends - that had the same interests as myself you see. That was the sort of thing that happened there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did your wife have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Not a lot,
 she had her friends there. But I - don't remember her ever making - a friend of any particular one. Before she was married - she had friends there but - they happened to get married the same time as she did, we did - and they went their way and we went o
ur way. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, if any of the friends that - she knew came along - we'd invite them there, they'd come there to tea probably on a Sunday sometimes. But it wasn't a regular thing. It was
n't a regular thing at all. We had plenty of friends - if you understand me, wherever we went, everybody knew us and we knew them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 But they didn't come back and forward to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh no, no. Well I didn't believe in that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would they come on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No. No. Any time they passed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you say that the friends invited in were your wife's friends or your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh my - my wife's friends more or less. More or less because I - as 
I told you - I - when I went there I had no friends up there. I was a perfect stranger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would any friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, like any - in the afternoon, if they were passing our house t
o go down the shop. They'd probably call in. Or if they were going home from the cinema or something and - the door was on the jar they'd pop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about neighbours now, would they call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh no. No, no, no, no
, no. Although mind - let me put to understand, the neighbours up there - were very very good neighbours. Real - old Welsh style people you know, that wanted to help if they could and anything, oh and if there was a - anybody ill or we'd one of the childr
en bad, oh they'd be back and fore in a minute to find out what was the matter and - but they never - opened the door and walked in - without there was something - special, something wrong. Oh they were - good neighbours though just the same you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No. No. Never. We'd go to the family, go out to - not friends, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 People often tell us that in these days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh well we did too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well, I mean -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When you were with friends or neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well - if you wanted to make - if you had any friends - you would either have a little sing-song, or you'd play games - the fields up here in where we were, we'd go up there a crowd of us very often. Yes, and play cricket and - have a little - old gram}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
phone up there and have a bit of music you know, have a dance. But - that was very seldom. Very seldom. You see we - we used to perform - a lot of cantatas in them days. And that was taki
ng up a lot of time sometimes and - my father-in-law happened to be the conductor of the - Baptist chapel there, and - he was running - an operetta society then, there was somebody else - running penny reading. Well we're somewhere or other - three or fou
r times a week. And the other nights of course, you had your darning and your sewing to do and your little bit of - with the children, so times are going very quick. You couldn't really find time to do everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes, they were - a lot of club houses, belonging to the colliery, that I was living in. Three rooms up, three down. No bathroom, we made our own bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Aye. Once a month. Once a month when he come to collect the rent. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Damned terrible. He was no good at all. He was prepared to collect the money but - never, they talk bout repairs today,
 God - you couldn't get nothing done. I remember on one occasion alone - we were in a terrible state, the water coming down in the back bedroom, and I had - and he lived in Llanduff here, that's the funny thing you know. Philip Jones. And I had persuaded 
h
im, asked him and coaxed him - about doing this - and one - month he - And - we had this water coming in. And I had asked him and asked him, no. So he came to collect the rent this here Monday, and I invited him into the parlour. And I walked up behind - 
i
n behind him and put the key in the door, locked the door. So he said - what's the matter then? Now, I said, before we go any father, what about this repairs? Well he tried to make all - well I said, there's no more - no rent for you - until they are done
.
 Then he wanted to say he couldn't get anybody to do it. So I was pretty handy myself, so I agreed to put a few slates on the roof providing he paid. So - he agreed to this. Well fair enough. So I paid the rent and let him go. Well the following day or pu
t
 the slates on the roof, and when he came the next - month, I had a bill for twelve and six, only twelve and six. And - when he came in, I gave him this bill, oh he couldn't pay that, he'd have to - send it to the - colliery and - I said, I've done the jo
b
 and I want the money now. And I - locked him in the front room. Went out and - left the key in the floor outside. Left him in there for half an hour, and he was knocking and shouting the door, so at last he said, well - let me out and I'll pay you. So I 
let him out and he paid me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 He was the agent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
The agent, yes, yes, that's all. Colliery house, aye. But oh - it was stinking for repairs. Oh. You couldn't - oh but mind they would - they wanted the rent all right. They'd have the rent off you. B
ut it was terrible, you couldn't get them to do nothing. And I remember one occasions - there was one or two people living there - that wasn't working in the colliery. And we were getting our light, electric light - from the colliery. But those - people l
i
ving next door to me - they were friends of ours, and - she was going to have a baby, and they weren't working in the colliery so they had no light. From the colliery. So - the husband and myself, we decided to try to fix it up with some lights. So we wen
t
 out through the windows, and - put rubber gloves on, we were scraping the electric wire outside, to tie a little bit of wire round it - to bring a lead into the bedroom. Oh, before we knew where we were we had all the street out, no lights, we had blew t
h
e damned lot. The next day, the - the - the electricians were up - looking at all the houses to see who had been tampering with 'em. And they never found it. We took the lead off, they never found out who done it. But that's the only - that's the thing - 
sort of thing we had to do. Oh it was very bad. Very bad up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 This is a different district from where you lived early, it's Tonyrfail now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - in - in Tonyre
fail it was a very funny thing. The doctors up there - were the most important people. Yes. There was no - there were no big - big people up there you see. There were no squire or - or alderman or anybody. The check - weighers in the colliery - they tried
 
to make themselves big pots you know. But they weren't so big as they thought they were. But the doctors in that place, there was a Doctor Braden there. Fine man. Irishman, had two lovely daughters and a wife. And he was a colliery doctor. And he was look
ed up to by everybody. Everybody, and then we had a -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why do you think he was looked up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well because he was one of the men - that they could tell their bits of trouble to, and if they sent for him, he'd come. He'd come, even down the pit he 
used to go. Oh yes. Yes, and his wife was as good as gold. She'd help as well. No, no, no, the - the - the funny thing about it do you see that - everybody in Tonyrefail in those days - seemed to be - very poor people, working class sort of people. There 
were no second and third class there at all, no. And the counsel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
ors as we had there, they were nobody. No one at all, nobody would take any notice of council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 ors we had. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you come into contact with the doctors there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh aye, and when you 
- matter of fact - I was very very friendly with him. Very friendly with him. He - I don't know why I'm sure. But - a couple of times I had to fetch him to my own children, and - he was fond of horses and I was fond of horses, and I had a couple of ponies
 at that time. And he was a very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017  be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 very interested. And his wife used to come up very often to have a look at a couple of ponies. Oh there's a - he was a nice man and a nice family altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about the shopkeepers in Tonyrefail, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well - there again you see, the shopkeepers - were just - ordinary people like ourselves. There were a greengrocers - big greengrocers shop in Tony, Bert Evans, well he had been a collier you see. And the old ironmonger, he had been a 
collier. And - wallpaper and that bloke, well he had been a collier. They - they were all more or less, there was only about - three shops then. Ton - that was - big shops, Thomas and Evans. Peglers. And Liptons. And they were only managers, so they were 
just ordinary people, they were no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
The clergy, ah now - the par - the vicar of Tonyrefail, we never seen him. And the preacher there that we had you know - the chapel that I went to myself, we didn't ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 e a - a preacher, 
supplies. No, no, no, no, no. No. And they had one in the Methodist church down below there, and - he was only quite a young - young man. Well he was - not a - not looked up to by anybody. He used to play about with the young men and - no, no, they weren'
t
 - but that's a funny thing, there was no one like - like in Tongwynlais see they - we had the squire there, and - he was looked up to by everybody. And fair play, the old vicar in our - in Tongwynlais, he - he was a very important man you see. Then we ha
d a - a man by the name of Talliasan Richard, a great man - with the ambulance brigade. Now he was look - he was agent o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
 a colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 That was in Tongwynlais?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about Tonyrefail, there was a vicar there was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Ah, but not 
- aye, a vicar, there was a - very seldom we saw him. No, he never mixed with anybody. He had a couple of - of curates they call 'em like you know that you'd see running about, but there again you see, they had been working on the pit and the curates they
 became. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh God. The teachers, one teacher I ever remember there being of any value at all. And that was England the schoolmaster. I don't remember 'em ever - having any teachers of any value. No, no, they were just 
ordinary girls and boys - it isn't like it is today you see, they were - went to school, they were a monitor for a while, what they call monitors, and they went on pupil teaching. And then when they be - had been there a couple of years they'd shift somew
here else, so you always had pupil teachers there. There were never no real good - never no real good teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were there any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh - aye, about three or four farmers there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh, damn, with nobody. They'd scrounge for every ha'penny they could get. Robbers they were. Rob - they were honest. Robbers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were there any employers there, colliery managers I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Aye, only - the - the agent and the manager, no. There was no - and the funny thing, th
ere was no building of any value there at all in them days see. No, no, no. It was a dead - hole, and - there was nobody - of any substance if you understand, me there. Nobody you could look up now. In other places you could - there is someone always. Lik
e, that everybody look up to. But in Tonyrefail, no. In my - own - own - own opinion about Tonyrefail, it was - it was a - a bed - of - Communists and working class. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What sort of people would you say went to the church there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well - thi
s is the - devil of a question to ask that is because - a fair lot should never have been going. And it was - well the church I went to, we were all - working in the colliery, all work -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 It was chapel you went to wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 I was thinking of the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh the church, well - well - I would say, if I had to say now - that it was either Conservatives of Liberals. Yes. You wouldn't see many Labour people going to church - church, and the church, there was never many in there
 at all. Oh no, no, no, no. There was a - nice lot - there were the doctors - Tonyrefail doctors and the schoolteachers and - they'd be church people. Oh yes. And some of the shopkeepers mind. They'd be church people. But - no, no, there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Was there a Catholic church there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Aye? Oh no. No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who would go to chapel, what sort of people would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh - the working class - there were - the chapel - we were all the - on the same level. There was nobody - greater than the 
other. I can't understand today you see - they look up to - well you've got a different class of schoolmaster today. You've got schoolmaster that have passed high, and they know what they're talking about. 'Course there's Labour leaders and Liberal leader
s
, the great trade unionist, well all this was in it's infancy in those days. You see, so it was - starting from scratch. That was the - no, it - it - it was a working class area altogether Tonyrefail was. Mind - we did have a band there and did have a mal
e voice choir there. Oh yes, had some wonder - there's plenty of talent there with singing and that you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 There was quite a lot of activity like that there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, yes, oh a lot of activity like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And you had penny readings of course there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, yes. And we had - we had a - cinema there in them days. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Would you say that all the people in the working class there had the same standard of living or would you say there was different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, no, I - I - no, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You did mention just now about the check}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 weighers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes, well you see, when you come - they were working class - but there was a section of people - who - sort of - office workers, check}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3679952\charrsid13850017 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 weighers, and little bits of bosses, they would
 - be a - a side - think themselves - a - a cut above - we people that were - working. Oh yes, they would - there - there - there was two separate classes there mind. Oh yes, yes, yes. Amongst the workers, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh yes. Oh in them days, yes, there was, oh yes. Yes, they were a carpenter or a fitter or a - engineer, you was - looked as something different to anybody else. Oh they were a little bit - and don't make any mistake, 
in them days a - labourer, a carpenter - or a bricklayer, or a fitter, they all had labourers. And damn they'd make you know that he was a labourer too. Oh yes, don't make any mistake about that. You were a lab -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 How would they show it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well, I 
mean - if there was - took the two men to do a job - they wouldn't do it with you. Oh no, they - oh go and get help, they'd send you to go and get another labourer to help 'em before they'd soil their hands to do it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were some families thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Oh there was a lot of families now - in our place at the time - though of as very rough people. We did have a lot of - very - a lot of Irish - Irish people and a - tremendous lot of people from Bristol. Oh. They 
came from Bristol in the 1914 war - to get out of the Army, and some of the buggers are still there. Old men of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 To go into the colliery was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. And - and the work they couldn't work for toffee, but they came there and were - and the
 colliery were glad to have 'em you see. Oh no end of Bristol people came - and London. But Bristol people, we had no end of Bristol people there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And you mentioned there were Irish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh God, aye, Irish be damned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you treat those people differently from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well I never had much - I never had much - of course - I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did people think of them as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes. Oh lord, aye, aye. There was one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why did they think they were like that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 There was one pa
rt of the - part of the - Tonyrefail, what they call Coedile, and I should imagine about five hundred houses there. And there was Irish - Scotch, Bristol, Cockneys, oh God. They were that - rough, they'd knock the damned door down and cut it up for firewo
o
d. Oh God and always fights there. Dear oh dear, fighting be damned. Real rough houses they was, there were - families which I can't - can't tell you their name, different families there. God on a Saturday night - there'd be on - there wasn't many police 
a
bout mind, they'd be fetching the police from everywhere to 'em. Terrible lot they were, terrible. Oh yes, we had a - a very rough lot of people in Tonyrefail, well I - I remember a football game coming there to play from Ton - from my own home town, Tong
w
ynlais. God. I don't know how many of 'em went from there with a - broken nose, broken arms, terrible it was you know. Terrible. And of course there was Golroch on top of here. Aye, and that was a damned rough house. Oh God aye. But - see the - money in t
hem days - was pretty good, remember that now. This is what you've got to remember. See now you're - there was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 I had the feeling Tonyrefail was poor then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. You see now - you see there was - they didn't go - if they didn't go to work, they
 were getting about - twenty-three bob a week. That was what they called the Loyd George award, the Buxton award, the Sankey award, all the grants of three and four bob a day - whether they went to work or not. Oh God, I've seen a amn go in there with his
 hat to pit - pit head, get the money, and raking the sovereigns in - into a bowler hat, and him and his three boy - boys. Oh there was money about then. Oh dear dear, aye, don't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 The pits were very busy in the war and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh God, you're
 telling me they were. Yes. And I - I - I often thought when I - went - went to the Army, shilling a day. And allowed three and six a week for your wife. Three and a tanner, you would salute about ten damned times to get that. And when you go to draw it y
o
u were in debt a couple of bob, you would get one and six. Oh God aye. War time. And mind - work was very bad there see. There was no other work. No, only the colliery see. Not 'til after the war when it began to build - houses in a couple of roads, and t
h
en there was a little bit of work coming to - of course the money wasn't so big on the - on - on that you see. Then when we had the strike see, later on - but from 1913 - to 1918 mind - there was a lot of money about the Valleys. Oh aye. People don't neve
r
 realize that - they talk about the money we're earning today. They were earning big money in them days. And there was - plenty of it about, and they spend it too mind. Oh God aye. Dear dear. They were better dressed - some of the people that were earning
 the big money then - were better dressed than any of 'em are today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Who would you say were the people earning the big money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well there's a family that had - father and sons you know. That's right, the sons, they'd be driving hard ahead and the
y'd be on the coalface together. Where there'd be a family of three or four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 And actual colliers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 You're telling - and good colliers yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Piecework it was you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh yes, all piecework see, and - and damn - they could work, and then 
when they was getting this here grant, this Buxton award and Sankey award and all that, see that's all coming in - you get four boys, well you're getting about six quid a week coming in for nothing. Whether they worked or not. Oh yes. But - oh they were s
hort in them days mind. By the war, yes, aye. I've seen me walking five mile for a loaf of bread. Yes, walked down Llantrisant. And I've walked a damned sight farther than that for a packet of fags. Aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Well - no, I didn't have a struggle but lots of people did. I was a - I was - working piecework myself, and - no, there were - I always managed to earn enough. But you had to work mind. Oh God. Throw out - twelve ton - doing a bit of ext
ra work overtime. Throw out a ten ton - truck of coal for one and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 What difference did it make if you were ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Well if you were ill or out of work of which I - touch wood I - didn't happen to me - we didn't have anything we'd
 have to go in debt for what you could get. 'Cos there was no money coming in. There was nothing coming - there was no relief of any kind in them days see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were you ever ill and unable to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 No, no. No. No, matter of fact - I was never ou
t of work. Because if ever I - got out of work, I'd buy a horse and cart or something and go out green gro - greengrocery. Always, yes. Even in later life now. If I - my work went a bit short or there were nothing doing and - I'd buy horse and cart and - 
load up with greengrocery and go around the houses selling greengrocery. Always. I was never on the dole. Never out of work. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 So you didn't ever have to ask for help from anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh no. No, no, no. No. Well you wouldn't have it if you did ask. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
They'd give you a ticket - probably for a couple of bob, half a crown probably to get a bit of food, that's all. No, well you wouldn't get nothing off the Guardians. Of course I remember when the first strike came, we opened soup ki
tchens up there. See, that's how they had to live then. Oh there are lots of people - there are lots of people that - did earn decent - big families - that earned decent money you see. They wound up - in a tremendous lot of debt. Oh God aye, because - tak
e Peglers and Thomas and Evan's, and - all those shops, they'd let you go in debt for about fifty or sixty pound. Oh God aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 That was a lot of money in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Oh telling me, yes. Lord alive yes. And - in - talk about Ton - Tapswell by here.
 Special - tinworks opposite the old iron works, that was a - they had a company shop. By the station at Tapswell. And you - would only get so much money, the rest would be - pay - put in the shop to have a bit of grocery by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Were you ever paid like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 Yes. Yes. Aye, the company shop in Tapswell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14495273 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 When you worked in the tinworks were you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7606694 HG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8662948\charrsid13850017 
Yes, and you could - yes, and you couldn't buy anywhere else. You'd go in there, if your pay was three pound eight, there'd be about two pound goi
ng into the shop probably and you get the one pound eight back. Yes. Oh the company shop it was and you - you paid for your groceries and the work. And in some places the rent as well.
